The paper discusses techniques for fast analytics on multi-dimensional data, which is a common problem in database systems. The paper specifically focuses on array databases and their in-situ mechanisms, parallel processing, and in-memory caching. The paper proposes a distributed framework for cost-based caching of multi-dimensional arrays in native format, which involves identifying cells to be cached locally and determining an optimal assignment of cells to nodes. This work involves distributed computing, caching, and data structures, which are all relevant to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.DB (Database), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
